        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate logic that can be reused across multiple queries or stored procedures. This specific function is designed to determine the validity of an invoice payment type based on certain criteria defined within the function's logic."
        }
